Rating: 3
I didn't have sherry vinegar and substituted a mixture of white vinegar and cooking (dry) sherry, which worked well. I used chicken thighs rather than chicken breasts (because that's what I had); if you do this you need to reduce the broiling time.

Rating: 2
I can't help but think that the amount of honey listed in the recipe is a mistake. To balance the acidity of the vinegar, I added 2 tablespoons (not teaspoons). Then as a matter of personal preference I increased the chicken broth to 1/2 cup. Even with the better balanced sauce, and even though I like how all the ingredients are every day kitchen staples, I can't help but think that this sauce would be better suited towards something gamier like duck or venison.

Rating: 3
