Rating: 0
Bev-I too had to go to 3 stores to find sherry vinegar, and I live in the land of upscale stores. When I found it was $7 a bottle, I passed. Anyway, we loved the dish but I made a few changes. Instead of sherry vinegar I used white wine vinegar and a generous glug of sherry. I also coated the chicken with flour (boneless and skinless by the way). My husband did add a sprinkling of Wondra flour to thicken a little at the end. Would make again in a heartbeat (but I won't rate the recipe since I changed it).

